  "sourceCode": "Employer Portal",
  "title": "IT Administrator",
  "description": "<h1>Key Responsibilities</h1>\n<ul>\n  <li>Maintain and update IT asset inventory records (e.g., laptops, accessories, software licenses) in accordance with WOG asset management guidelines.</li>\n  <li>Track issuance, transfer, and return of IT equipment for users, ensuring proper documentation and accountability.</li>\n  <li>Raise, update, and monitor service requests in the ITSM portal for procurement, support, and access requirements.</li>\n  <li>Coordinate with vendors for quotations, deliveries, and invoice processing.</li>\n  <li>Maintain documentation of IT policies, user guides, and standard operating procedures (SOPs).</li>\n  <li>Log and follow up on IT support issues, escalating when necessary.</li>\n  <li>Support user onboarding and offboarding processes, including account setup and asset handling.</li>\n  <li>Schedule and coordinate IT-related meetings, briefings, and training sessions.</li>\n  <li>Prepare and submit monthly IT reports covering asset status, service request metrics, and pending actions.</li>\n  <li>Handle general administrative tasks such as filing, data entry, and correspondence.</li>\n</ul>\n<h1>Key Requirements</h1>\n<ul>\n  <li>Prior experience in a WOG environment or familiarity with WOG IT processes preferred.</li>\n  <li>Proficiency in Microsoft Office (Excel, Word, Outlook).</li>\n  <li>Strong organisational skills and attention to detail.</li>\n  <li>Effective verbal and written communication skills.</li>\n  <li>Basic knowledge of IT systems and terminology.</li>\n  <li>Experience with ITSM tools such as ServiceNow and BMC will be an advantage.</li>\n</ul>",
  "minimumYearsExperience": 3,
